            obj_to_array: function(obj)
            {
                var array = [];
                angular.forEach(obj, function(value){
                    array.push(value);
                });
                return array;
            }
```
But I'm experiencing performances issues since I deal with large data sets. I think this is the wrong way to have : 
- my object of objects
- an array which is a copy of previous object
- smart table which makes its own safe copy
So memory management is far from being optimal with all those copies and watchers ....

I feel like I have 2 choices : 
- change my server data source from object to array but I don't like the idea since my services are made for objects and I like its simplicity  
- change smart-table to another table which handles objects (if I can found any) but I don't like this idea neither since I like smart-table and I was able to manage almost everything I need ... every choice is a bad choice in my case ;)

Thanks for your concern !

