@eLRuLL yeah, that kind of duplication (static version number in installation script and inside the module) is normal and sort of the reason bumpversion exists.
When you run `bumpversion minor`, it will increase the version number for a minor release (like, if it was 0.1.0 it will be 0.2.0) in all configured files (including its own config), create a commit and tag it.

